ance to the Great Stanišovská cave was closed. Malá Stanišovská cave is currently in the care of active local cavers, who themselves undertook to save it from further damage. Currently, there is a parking lot near the cave where you can park your car and a renovated cottage where you can buy tickets. Visitors to the cave have the opportunity to admire the underground natural beauty and learn about the basic aspects of cave exploration and speleology. The decoration of the cave is made up mainly of sinter deposits. In spring, ice stalagmites form in the entrance areas. The cave is of medium difficulty. There are no concrete sidewalks or significant landscaping. The bottom of the cave is covered with clay and stony rubble, in places with larger collapsed boulders. The cave is not lit. Each visitor from the guide has a headlamp and lights the way himself. So much with the available information. Near the cave there is a sign indicating a scooter track, and to the right of the sign there is a memorial to the victims of people who died in the forests of Jánská dolina and its surroundings. I recommend travelers to visit the cave and shrine, as well as use the scooter track. When you enter the cave, you will find a lot of information on the information boards about the cave and the lives of people who were and are forever connected to this place. Unforgettable memories will remain with you forever. You will not regret the time you spent getting to know this place. Open daily, admission every hour + individual admissions Admission: 10°° - 11°° - 12°° - 13°° - 14°° - 15°° - 16°° hrs. Adults - EUR 6, pensioners and children - EUR 3.50 Residents Lipt. Jána and Smrečian (identity card required) - 1 EURO Note: Ticket sales are ongoing or 10 to 5 min. before entry. Regular entry is every full hour. The cave manager can also allow another entrance if necessary. Please wait for the guide's return during the absence. Special entry: Maximum 20 people - EUR 100 Information by phone: +4